From 87c980149a1ba40b5d5f335b24e5a0740576099e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 13:30:58 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] airoha: an7563: disable U-Boot UBI command and driver support

The AN7563 EVB SPI-NAND uses a pure raw MTD layout with the
Airoha BMT bad-block layer underneath; there is no UBI on the
boot-side partitions (u-boot, u-boot-env, art, fip), and after
the previous patch ("store env in raw 'u-boot-env' MTD
partition") even the U-Boot environment is no longer kept in
UBI.

Drop the now-unused UBI command, MTD-UBI driver and UBIFS
options from the AN7563 EVB defconfig:

  -CONFIG_CMD_UBI=y
  -# CONFIG_CMD_UBI_RENAME is not set
  -CONFIG_CMD_UBIFS=y
  -CONFIG_MTD_UBI=y
  -CONFIG_MTD_UBI_MODULE=y
  -CONFIG_MTD_UBI_WL_THRESHOLD=4096
  -CONFIG_MTD_UBI_BEB_LIMIT=20
  -# CONFIG_MTD_UBI_FASTMAP is not set
  -CONFIG_UBI_BLOCK=y
  -# CONFIG_UBIFS_SILENCE_MSG is not set
  -# CONFIG_UBIFS_SILENCE_DEBUG_DUMP is not set

This shrinks the U-Boot binary by skipping the UBI scan/attach
code paths that would never run on this board layout, and
avoids surprising U-Boot prompt commands ('ubi part', 'ubi
read', 'ubifsls', ...) that could only ever fail.

Linux side stays as-is: OpenWrt overlayfs / sysupgrade may
still want UBI on the kernel side, so target/linux/airoha
keeps CONFIG_MTD_UBI* / UBIFS / UBI_BLOCK enabled.

Signed-off-by: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
---
 configs/an7563_evb_defconfig | 11 -----------
 1 file changed, 11 deletions(-)

diff --git a/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig b/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig
index 8bf8f8f5..750821d5 100644
--- a/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig
+++ b/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig
@@ -67,17 +67,6 @@ CONFIG_SYS_NS16550=y
 CONFIG_SPI=y
 CONFIG_DM_SPI=y
 CONFIG_AIROHA_SNFI_SPI=y
-CONFIG_CMD_UBI=y
-# CONFIG_CMD_UBI_RENAME is not set
-CONFIG_CMD_UBIFS=y
-CONFIG_MTD_UBI=y
-CONFIG_MTD_UBI_MODULE=y
-CONFIG_MTD_UBI_WL_THRESHOLD=4096
-CONFIG_MTD_UBI_BEB_LIMIT=20
-# CONFIG_MTD_UBI_FASTMAP is not set
-CONFIG_UBI_BLOCK=y
-# CONFIG_UBIFS_SILENCE_MSG is not set
-# CONFIG_UBIFS_SILENCE_DEBUG_DUMP is not set
 CONFIG_ENV_USE_DEFAULT_ENV_TEXT_FILE=y
 CONFIG_ENV_DEFAULT_ENV_TEXT_FILE="defenvs/an7563_rfb_env"
 CONFIG_SHA512=y
